name: Homicide
overview: Homicide was an Australian television police drama series  The series dealt with the homicide squad of the Victorian Police force and the various crimes and cases the detectives are called upon to investigate. Many episodes were based on real life crime cases.

episodes.name: The Stunt
episodes.overview: A group of students stage a mock bank hold-up to publicise a charity. When the students' leader is shot dead by a bank guard, Homicide detectives have to establish whether the guard was acting within his duty or recklessly; a complication is that jealousy in the group caused the student to be 'set up' for the shooting.

episodes.name: A Handful Of Money
episodes.overview: An old couple who run a milk bar in an inner suburb are found brutally murdered. A young man is charged, and confesses, but Det. Sgt. Bronson's doubts about his guilt still complicate the issue, and bring he and Insp. Connolly into conflict.

episodes.name: The Rosary
episodes.overview: For three days, a cottage in the Dandenong Ranges provides a perfect honeymoon hideaway. But then the young bride is brutally slain, and Homicide detectives find themselves investigating bigamy as well as murder.

episodes.name: The Knot
episodes.overview: An unidentified young woman is murdered in a park, the second such occurrence, and Homicide detectives have to race against time to prevent a third killing.

episodes.name: The Man In The Suede Jacket
Aunt Sally
episodes.overview: A clerk is shot when two masked men hold up a factory and steal a $10,000 payroll. Homicide detectives have no real leads, and must rely on information from an informer, Sgt. Bronson's 'Aunt Sally'.

episodes.name: The Scent Of Death
episodes.overview: A body is discovered in a railway box-car at the Jolimont railway yards, from where a young boy has also gone missing. Police dogs are called in to track down the killer, a young man who has killed his father with an iron bar during an argument, and fled with the only witness - the missing boy.

episodes.name: The Missing Letter
episodes.overview: Edward Heywood is reported missing, and three weeks later his body is recovered from the Yarra River.  Two anonymous letters - death threats - provide the Homicide detectives with an important clue. The man's wife, Katarina, had many lovers, and when she reports her sister-in-law Norma has suicided, one of her lovers, Rogowski, makes a false confession.

episodes.name: The Silent Witness
episodes.overview: When an attractive young girl is murdered, it doesn't take long for the Homicide detectives to identify her killer; but they have a tense time gathering sufficient evidence to bring him to trial, aware that before they can complete their case he may well kill again.

episodes.name: The Hook
episodes.overview: A man dies a violent death aboard a boat at dawn.  Although there is an eye-witness, he claims he was too far away to identify the killer, and the Homicide detectives have some fast thinking to do as they pursue their suspects around the confusing world of the waterfront.

episodes.name: Manhunt
episodes.overview: When William Nelson blows up the car of a business acquaintance, killing him, he is quickly brought to justice, and sentenced to serve a life sentence for murder. However, Nelson is cunning and resourceful, and escapes from custody â€“ and it is not only his freedom he wants, but a chance to even up the score against the main prosecution witness.

episodes.name: The Decimal Point
episodes.overview: A convict who has broken out of jail is murdered at the rendezvous with an accomplice, and Det. Sgt. Bronson suspects that there is a connection between his death and an unsolved  robbery committed five years earlier.

episodes.name: Aftermath
episodes.overview: Retired Inspector Bob Fenton, former chief of the Homicide squad, is fatally stabbed and his body left in the driveway of the home of Insp. Connolly. Fenton appears to have been the victim of revenge, and Connolly realises that he could be the next target.

episodes.name: The White Mistress
episodes.overview: The Homicide squad has help from the Forensic division when investigating the death of a woman who had apparently ceased to exist a year before being killed.

episodes.name: The Violaters
episodes.overview: Matters are complicated for the police when a young girl shirks from the publicity she fears will result if she makes known the full story of her abduction and gang rape, following the revenge which was meted out to her assailants.

episodes.name: The Partners
episodes.overview: A man found dead in a burnt out car at the foot of a cliff is presumed to be the owner, James Bannister.  But further evidence points to Bannister still being alive, and detectives gradually unravel an insurance fraud which ends in another murder.

episodes.name: The Brand
episodes.overview: When Homicide detectives probe the underworld to investigate the murder of a prostitute, they find the dead girl's friends and accomplices all fear for their own lives. Their investigations are complicated by an obvious crank with a passion for reforming people.

episodes.name: Love Is On A Silver Chain
Have You Heard About The Laurences?
There Are More Things In Heaven And Earth
Tom Mitchell's Money Box
episodes.overview: Gordon Bishop is a drifter, moving from place to place and job to job. He dreams of a big win at the races, or, even better, at a gambling casino. He also owns a .38 revolver, and when his former employers, milk bar proprietors Tom and Alice Mitchell, are found shot by a .38 with their life savings gone from their cash box, Bishop becomes the prime suspect. Damning evidence mounts up against him; then a girlfriend informs police that he has taken off for Wrest Point Casino with a large 'killing' he claims he won at the races. The Tasmanian police apprehend Bishop, the last formality of an identification parade is arranged, and the case is all ready to be sewn up.  But then the witness fails to pick out Bishop from the parade...

episodes.name: Shut Your Mouth And You'll Catch No Flies
I Keep Going Back To Be Certain
The Animal That Has To Be Fed
The Life And Times Of Tina Kennedy
You Probably Won't Believe This, But
Leader Of The Pack
episodes.overview: Luke, the fanatical leader of a religious cult, kidnaps Kim Clayton, daughter of a newspaper magnate, after her 18th birthday party. The Homicide squad's investigations are hampered when her father pays the $100,000 ransom.

episodes.name: Stopover
episodes.overview: Denny Connell, a member of Gordon Haynes' pop group, dies of a massive heroin overdose on arrival at Melbourne's Tullamarine Airport. Haynes is a 30-year-old pop star whose career has been a succession of hits and crashes. He has been written off many times but has come back - only to crash again. As the investigation progresses, it becomes clear that Connell was murdered, and many motives and suspects emerge. Inspector Lawson goes to London to investigate further, where he liases with Inspector Scofield of Scotland Yard. A few twists are in store before the Homicide squad finally unravel the solution.
